          "settings": {
            "question": "Will full-spectrum CBD make me fail a drug test?",
            "answer": "<p>It’s rare, but possible. Our <a href=\"https://kushqueen.shop/products/full-spectrum-cbd-chews\" title=\"https://kushqueen.shop/products/full-spectrum-cbd-chews\">full-spectrum CBD gummies</a> contain only trace amounts of THC (within the legal limit), but if you’re taking high doses consistently, there’s a slim chance it could show up on a drug test. If this is a big concern, we recommend going with a broad-spectrum or THC-free option just to be extra safe.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_block_WbqHam": {
          "type": "faq_block",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How should I take my CBD gummies for the best effect?",
            "answer": "<p>It’s simple—pop a gummy and see how you feel! If you’re new to CBD, start with one gummy and give it about an hour to work its magic. You can adjust from there depending on your needs. Consistency is key, so taking your gummies around the same time each day can help you enjoy those long-term benefits.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_block_NKEgnq": {
          "type": "faq_block",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are CBD gummies legal in my state?",
            "answer": "<p>Maybe! CBD from hemp (with less than 0.3% THC) is federally legal, thanks to the 2018 Farm Bill. Most states allow CBD, but it’s always smart to double-<a href=\"https://www.fda.gov/news-events/public-health-focus/fda-regulation-cannabis-and-cannabis-derived-products-including-cannabidiol-cbd\" title=\"https://www.fda.gov/news-events/public-health-focus/fda-regulation-cannabis-and-cannabis-derived-products-including-cannabidiol-cbd\">check local regulations</a> if you’re unsure.</p>"
          }
        },
